remove dependency on python3-six and python2 crumbs

python3-six is a deprecated transition layer
that was once usefull to make codebases work with both python 2 & 3

------------------------------------------------------------------

Libbytesize 2.0
---------------

**Notable changes**

- Python 2 support has been removed.

Merge pull request #131 from tbzatek/automake-errors

build: Exit before AC_OUTPUT on error

commit.message:
build: Exit before AC_OUTPUT on error

In case of configure failures an exit code 1 will be returned, yet
it's apparently not always checked by distributors. And since
AC_OUTPUT has already generated target Makefiles, some issues like
a missing pcre library (that expands to an empty string) may not
cause immediate build failure yet the generated object files may
not be entirely valid.
tests: fix locale tests on musl
